<h1>The First All-Girls Public School In Missouri</h1>
<p>Welcome to Hawthorn Leadership School for Girls! Hawthorn is the only public all-girls school in Missouri. We provide middle and high school girls a high quality, college preparatory education with a particular focus on STEM (science, technology, engineering and math). Hawthorn opened in 2015 with 120 6th and 7th grade girls. The school will add a new sixth grade each school year until 2020 when we will be fully enrolled with approximately 450 girls in 6th – 12th grades.</p>
<p>Hawthorn is the first school of its kind, an all-girls’ public charter school offering all St. Louis families the opportunity to choose a single-sex school for their middle and high school daughters. Hawthorn provides young women with the academic background, self-esteem, and leadership skills that will enable them to succeed in college and beyond.</p>
<p><a href="/covid-19.html">Click here for COVID-19 updates from Hawthorn. </a></p>
<p> </p>
<p><em>In accordance with Missouri law, for information on the Missouri Course Access Program (MOCAP), see the <a href="/cmss_files/attachmentlibrary/Virtual-Education-Policy-new--amp--revised-Sept-2019.docx" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Hawthorn Virtual Education Policy</a>.</em></p>
