<h2>Culture</h2>
<p>Hawthorn Leadership School for Girls is a college preparatory school with a rigorous academic program. The faculty and staff of Hawthorn sets high expectations inside and outside the classroom and provides the academic and developmental support to reach those expectations.</p>
<p>At Hawthorn, we realize that supporting the "whole girl" is essential to our students’ growth and development into competent, confident young women. We have the people and structures in place to meet girls where they are and work with them to build self-esteem, healthy relationships and to make good choices.</p>
<p class="text-center"><a class="btn" data-text="Learn More" href="/being-a-hawthorn-girl.html" title="Being a Hawthorn Girl"><span>Learn More</span></a></p>
</div>
</div>
</section><section class="stem"><div class="row">
<div class="medium-5 medium-offset-1 columns">
<h2>Stem</h2>
<p>Hawthorn's curriculum has a particular focus on STEM: science, technology, engineering and math to best prepare our students for the career opportunities of the future and to aim to close the STEM gender gap. Beginning in middle school, the curriculum includes two periods of math, as well as introductory programming. The STEM courses are typically taught from an interdisciplinary approach and required work is complete within project teams, similar to real world work environments.</p>
<p class="text-center"><a class="btn" data-text="Learn More" href="http://www.hawthornschool.org/curriculum.html" title="Our Curiculum"><span>Learn More</span></a></p>
</div>
<div class="medium-5 columns end show-for-medium-up">
